T: l^2 \to l^2
Tx = y =(\eta_j)
x = (\xi_j)
T
 \eta_j = \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \alpha_{jk}\xi_k, \quad \quad \sum_{j=1}^{\infty} \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} |\alpha_{jk}|^2 < \infty. 
T_n x = (\sum_{k=1}^{n} \alpha_{1k}\xi_k, \sum_{k=1}^{n} \alpha_{2k}\xi_k, \sum_{k=1}^{n} \alpha_{3k}\xi_k, \ldots)
T_n
\mathrm{dim} \, T_n(X) < \infty
T_n
 ||(T-T_n)x^2|| = \sum_{j=n+1}^{\infty}\sum_{k=n+1}^{\infty} |\eta_j|^2 = \sum_{j=n+1}^{\infty}\sum_{k=n+1}^{\infty} |\alpha_{jk}|^2 |\xi_k|^2. 
